    "recap_headline": "Sacred Heart",
    "recap_text": "Brighton, Mass. \u2013\nSacred Heart struck early and stayed within reach, highlighted by\nPeter Link's\nlate home run, but Boston College held on to secure the win.\nRecords\nSacred Heart | 4-13 (3-3 MAAC)\nBoston College | 12-8 (3-3 ACC)\nTop Performers\nPeter Link\n: 2-3, R, 2 RBI, double, HR\nRonan Donohue\n: 1-3, 2 R, RBI, HR\nJacob Schmutz\n: 1-4, R, double\nAiden Emrich\n: 1.1 IP, 3 H, 2 R, 1 SO\nJase Schueller\n: 2.2 IP, 2 H, 1 R, 1 SO\nHow It Happened\nSacred Heart struck first in the opening inning when Schmutz doubled and moved to third on a wild pitch before scoring on a sacrifice fly by\nWill Cook\n.\nBoston College responded quickly, scoring a run in the first and adding another in the second to take the lead. The Eagles extended their advantage in the fourth after\nPeter Link\ndoubled in the top half, but the Pioneers were unable to capitalize.\nRonan Donohue\nprovided a spark in the sixth inning with a solo home run to keep Sacred Heart within reach. Boston College answered again in the seventh, plating two runs to push its lead further.\nThe Pioneers made a late push in the eighth when\nRonan Donohue\ndrew a walk and\nPeter Link\nfollowed with a two-run home run, but Sacred Heart could not complete the comeback.\nUp Next\nThe Pioneers travel to Smithfield, Rhode Island for a weekend series against Bryant, with the first two games on the road before returning for their home opener at Veterans Park on Sunday. First pitch is set for 3 p.m. Friday and 1 p.m. on both Saturday and Sunday."
